xwikidoc.title: WebFolders
xwikidoc.content:
{{info}} The WebFolders client does not provide a complete file system like abstraction to a WebDAV share. {{/info}}
{{warning}} For a list of known issues with the WebFolders client, please refer to [[this list>>http://www.greenbytes.de/tech/webdav/webfolder-client-list.html]]. {{/warning}}
On windows XP, there are several ways you can access a remote webdav server. WebFolders is the most basic one.
* First, you need to open the **My Network Places** view. For this navigate to **Start->My Network Places**. [[image:Features.WebDAVWebFolders@MyNetworkPlaces.png]]
* On the upper left corner of the task panel, click on the **Add Network Place** task. This should open up a wizard, click **Next**.[[image:Features.WebDAVWebFolders@AddNetworkPlaceWiz1.png]]
* After some processing, you will be directed to the next screen. Here, you must select **Choose another network location** and click **Next**.[[image:Features.WebDAVWebFolders@AddNetworkPlaceWiz2.png]]
* On the next screen you must specify the network path to your xwiki webdav server. By default this is ##http:~/~/<xwikihost>/xwiki/webdav/##. Once you are done, click **Next**. [[image:Features.WebDAVWebFolders@AddNetworkPlaceWiz3.png]]
* Here you'll be asked to provide login details for the xwiki webdav server. Use your login details for the corresponding xwiki server and click **Next**. [[image:Features.WebDAVWebFolders@AddNetworkPlaceWiz4.png]]
* Give your new network place a name and click **Next**. [[image:Features.WebDAVWebFolders@AddNetworkPlaceWiz5.png]]
* There you go! Your new network place should now be enlisted under **My Network Places**. [[image:Features.WebDAVWebFolders@NewConnection.png]]
* Ok then, time to start browsing! [[image:Features.WebDAVWebFolders@XPBrows.png]]
